Thus the grammar does generate “t3 t2.”

The only nonterminal that can directly produce “t7” is NT33 (via NT33 → 't7'), but its partner NT24 cannot produce “t7” in one step (its direct terminals are 't3','t0','t2').  The other option, NT7 NT20, fails because neither NT7 nor NT20 has a direct production to 't7'.  Any longer derivation would yield more than two terminals.
